<hl>
<seg id=1> China Plans to Fill Millions Hectares of Sea Next Century, Settle 20 or 30 Million People. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Agence Francaise de Press, Beijing) - English version "China Daily" reported yesterday, China plans to fill millions hectares of sea next century and to settle 20 or 30 million people. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Specialists revealed in an earth-filling meeting held on Xiaoshan of Zhejiang province, government hopes to fill one million hectares of sea along 18,000 kilometer long in 40 or 50 years. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "China Daily" said that 20 or 30 million people will live in these areas next century. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> This newspaper cited Professor Yu Zhiyin's speech: "From the technical point of view, it is not a problem for China to fill the sea, the question is the capital." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The source said, even this plan will cause a big environmental problem, "This is still a good method to ease up the insufficient land resources next century, particularly because China has such a big population." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The relevant plan can also promote new industry and employment opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=8> China plans to invest on infrastructure to eliminate the impact of Asian financial crises. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Zuo Zhongmo(transliteration), deputy secretary general of the meeting said:" This is not only a agricultural issue, these land can be used for comprehensive developing applications in many fields, including forestry, industry and tourism." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Although China carries out "One child policy", China's population is estimated to grow continuously till the middle of next century. It will reach its maximum of 1.6 billion populations. </seg>
<seg id=11> China now has 1.23 billion populations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Over 90% population concentrates on one-third country land. </seg>
</p>
